A–C), slightly behind VFO in most individuals (

) or nearly at same vertical in some, predorsal length 1.6 (1.5–1.6). Pectoral fin level with vertical of posterior margin of gill cover, its upper base about level with lower margin of eye. A small pocket behind pectoral-fin base. VFO slightly behind midpoint of SL, prepelvic length 1.6 (1.6–1.7) in SL, with a small axial scale behind pelvic fin base. Anal fin originating at posterior fourth of body, preanal length 1.3 (1.2–1.3). Anal-fin base 6.5 (6.4–7.9) in SL. Adipose fin above rear portion of anal-fin base.

Moreover, the northwestern Pacific Ocean population (e.g. from Taiwan , Japan and the Philippines ) is now recognised as a distinct species (
Ho et al. , 2019a
), representing Ege’s moderately high vertebral number population. Specimens of the low vertebral number population are needed for further study.

